tool.help:
**What it does**
For an input GFF3, this tool specifically removes the feature entry with remark type (column 3) as needed for compatibility with certain tools. The remark feature typically encompasses the entire length of the sequence upon which the GFF3 is based.
Example input:: Miro annotation remark 1 167935 . . . gff-version=3;sequence-region=%28%27Miro%27%2C 0%2C 172788%29 Miro cpt gene 1231 5436 . . . ID=CDS1;
Example output:: Miro cpt gene 1231 5436 . . . ID=CDS1;
